0.gif#h=150&w=208", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd408:g4084:g4084d:pm006910/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=864&w=1198", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd408:g4084:g4084d:pm006910/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=1728&w=2396"], "index": 1, "language": ["english"], "location": ["ohio", "dayton", "united states"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/tiff", "image/jpeg", "image/jp2"], "number": ["73694508", "2025-06-07t18:29:52.600000", "2005-01-05t17:23:15"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["map"], "partof": ["catalog", "panoramic maps", "geography and map division", "cities and towns"], "score": 28.969477, "shelf_id": "G4084.D2A3 1870 .R8", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["ohio", "united states", "aerial views", "dayton", "dayton (ohio)"], "timestamp": "2026-04-29T16:12:55.935Z", "title": "Dayton, Ohio 1870", "type": ["cartographic"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/73694508/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2023275556", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2023275556/", "http://public.eblib.com/choice/PublicFullRecord.aspx?p=4854546"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["bowditch, eden unger"], "date": "2017", "dates": ["2017"], "description": ["\"After an exciting but stressful year and a half, the Young Inventors Guild members finally reunite with their parents, who had continually evidenced a disturbing tendency to go missing. The families head to Cairo, Egypt, to see Noah's mother, the magnificent Ariana Canto-Sagas, perform on the famous opera stage there. But danger arrives in the form of the ever-elusive but always-present Komar Romak. Running out of time, Jasper, Lucy, Faye, Wallace, and Noah must extract key information hidden in the pages of a time, and combine it with their remarkable talents for invention\"--Back cover"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-02-27T06:55:34.271Z", "group": ["catalog-split-05", "catalog", "main-catalog-split-05"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2023275556", "image_url": [], "index": 2, "language": ["english"], "location": ["ohio", "dayton"], "number": ["n1001550887", "2023275556", "2025-02-25t14:19:21"], "original_format": ["book"], "other_title": ["Poet, the king, and the mysterious men in black"], "partof": ["catalog"], "score": 25.739012, "shelf_id": "PN6071.D45 B693 2017", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["young adult fiction", "juvenile works", "secrecy", "juvenile fiction", "fiction", "inventions", "romans, nouvelles, etc. pour la jeunesse", "ohio", "young adult works", "dayton", "kidnapping", "detective and mystery fiction", "secret", "dayton (ohio)"], "timestamp": "2025-02-27T06:56:53.420Z", "title": "Strange round bird : or the poet, the king, and the mysterious men in black", "type": ["text"], "url": "//lccn.loc.gov/2023275556"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/mm78046706", "http://www.loc.gov/item/mm78046706/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.mss/collmss.ms000022"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["mcfarland, marvin wilks", "wright, orville", "wright, milton", "wright and wright", "wright cycle company", "united states. national advisory committee for aeronautics", "wright, wilbur"], "description": ["Correspondence, diaries, minutes, notebooks, writings, reports, business and legal papers, genealogical material, printed matter, patents, blueprints, photographs, and other papers relating primarily to the invention of the airplane and the development of aviation.  Documents the lives and work of the Wright brothers who designed, built, and piloted the first machine to achieve powered, sustained flight in 1903 and the first practical airplane in 1905. The papers include scientific data, formulas, and computations related to aerodynamic and design factors and describe the brothers' experimentation with flight at Kitty Hawk, N.C., 1900-1903, at College Park, Md., in 1909, and at Montgomery, Ala., in 1910, and their trips abroad making flight demonstrations.  Subjects include the sale of the Wright airplane to the U.S. Army and others; business concerns involving the Wright Company, Flint and Company, Brewer and Son, Thierry Brothers, and companies established in Great Britain, France, and Germany to produce and sell Wright aircraft; the Wright brothers' patents in the U.S. and abroad as well as airplane patents by others; and the brothers' dispute with Smithsonian Institution over whether S.P. Langley had created an aircraft capable of flight prior to the Wrights' flight in December 1903. Also includes journals and ledgers from Wright and Wright printing company and Wright Cycle Company; records of the U.S. National Advisory Committee for Aeronautics; typescripts, research material, and photographs collected for The Papers of Wilbur and Orville Wright, edited by Marvin Wilks McFarland and published in 1953; and Wright family papers including transcripts of Milton Wright's diaries, 1901-1907.  The 2019 Addition includes a 1919 letter from Orville Wright concerning his test flight of the first military airplane, Signal Corps No. 1, on July 30, 1909. Wright family correspondents include Katharine Wright Haskell, Lorin Wright, Milton Wright, and Reuchlin Wright.  Other correspondents include Henry Harley Arnold, Hart O. Berg, Griffith Brewer, Octave Chanute, Robert J. Collier, Earl N. Findley, Benjamin D. Foulois, Fred C. Kelly, Roy Knabenshue, Frank Purdy Lahm, Charles A. Lindbergh, Grover Cleveland Loening, Glenn L. Martin, Charles Stewart Rolls, G.A. Spratt, Paul Tissandier, Harry A. Toulmin, and Pliny W. Williamson."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-04-30T05:56:07.865Z", "group": ["catalog-split-00", "catalog", "main-catalog-split-00"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/mm78046706", "image_url": [], "index": 3, "language": ["german", "french", "english"], "location": ["montgomery", "great britain", "kitty hawk", "ohio", "united states", "france", "maryland", "dayton", "north carolina", "college park", "germany", "alabama"], "number": ["2025-04-28t11:22:12", "mm78046706"], "original_format": ["manuscript/mixed material", "collection"], "other_title": ["Wilbur and Orville Wright papers", "Wilbur Wright papers", "Orville Wright papers"], "partof": ["catalog", "manuscript division"], "score": 23.442888, "shelf_id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/mm78046706", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["wright company", "procurement", "martin, glenn l.", "rolls, charles stewart", "wright, milton", "united states", "aircraft industry", "ohio", "signal corps no. 1 (airplane)", "correspondence", "patents", "haskell, katharine wright", "kelly, fred c.", "knabenshue, roy", "williamson, pliny w.", "samuel pierpont)", "great britain", "arnold, henry harley", "kitty hawk (n.c.)", "montgomery (ala.)", "smithsonian institution", "collier, robert j.", "fred charters)", "airplanes", "wright family", "spratt, g. a.", "germany", "printing", "robert joseph)", "findley, earl n.", "aeronautics", "langley, s. p.", "wright flyer (airplane)", "army", "history", "lindbergh, charles a.", "toulmin, harry a.", "earl nelson)", "harry aubrey)", "france", "bicycle industry", "glenn luther)", "thierry brothers", "dayton", "wright, lorin", "flint and company", "lahm, frank purdy", "flight", "wright, reuchlin", "tissandier, paul", "brewer, griffith", "loening, grover", "brewer and son", "george alexander)", "college park (md.)", "charles augustus)", "berg, hart o.", "foulois, benjamin d.", "chanute, octave"], "timestamp": "2025-04-30T05:58:59.353Z", "title": "Wilbur Wright and Orville Wright papers, 1809-1979", "type": ["manuscript"], "url": "//lccn.loc.gov/mm78046706"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/wri/item/2001696281/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2001696281/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2001696281/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/ppprs.00485", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/ppprs.00485/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2001696281"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": 