/batch_ohi_foxglove_ver01/data/sn84024221/00340580084/1946040801/0930.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ohi:batch_ohi_foxglove_ver01:data:sn84024221:00340580084:1946040801:0930/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_foxglove_ver01/data/sn84024221/00340580084/1946040801/0930.pdf", "segment_count": 4, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84024221/1946-04-08/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_foxglove_ver01/data/sn84024221/00340580084/1946040801/0930.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ohi:batch_ohi_foxglove_ver01:data:sn84024221:00340580084:1946040801:0930/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_foxglove_ver01/data/sn84024221/00340580084/1946040801/0930.pdf", "segment_count": 4, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84024221/1946-04-08/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_foxglove_ver01/data/sn84024221/00340580084/1946040801/0930.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84024221/1946-04-08/ed-1/?sp=1"], "batch": ["ohi_foxglove_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/ohio/", "2/united states/ohio/montgomery/", "3/united states/ohio/montgomery/dayton/"], "contributor": ["ohio history connection, columbus, oh"], "date": "1946-04-08", "dates": ["1946-04-08"], "description": ["FAIR FEARLESS ONE OF ENROLLMENT IN NEGRO SCHOOLS REACH PEAK YEAR WASHINGTON Apr 8 ANP A peak enrollment in Negro col leges and universities throughout the country has been reached ac cording to a recent survey conduct ed by Dr Martin D Jenkins a rep resentative of Howard universitys department of education One hundred eight institutions report a total of 43868 resident college student during the fall term of the current school year includ ing 41741 undergraduates the survey revealed which is an in crease of 16 per cent over the same term of last year Almost all insti tutions reported a gain in enroll ment over last year Dr Jenkins said Although some gain in male un dergraduates is reported male stu dents constitute only 22 per cent of the total whereas in prewar years they were about 45 per cent of the total enrollment Private institutions represent 54 per cent of the total enrollment of which 62 per cent are in fully accredited in stitutions The report published in the spring issue of the Journal of Ne gro BJducation published by the bureau of educational research of Howard university reveals that Howard is the largest institution reporting an"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-09-04T23:18:08.736Z", "group": ["ndnp/ohi", "ohio-historical-society-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84024221/1946-04-08/ed-1/?sp=1", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ohi:batch_ohi_foxglove_ver01:data:sn84024221:00340580084:1946040801:0930/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=406&w=272", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ohi:batch_ohi_foxglove_ver01:data:sn84024221:00340580084:1946040801:0930/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=812&w=544", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_foxglove_ver01/data/sn84024221/00340580084/1946040801/0930.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 1, "language": ["english"], "location": ["dayton", "montgomery", "ohio", "united states"], "location_city": ["dayton"], "location_country": ["united states"], "location_county": ["montgomery"], "location_state": ["ohio"], "mime_type": ["image/jp2", "ap